Description: Rim sherd of Attic black-figured pottery skyphos; interior: top of rim reserved, glazed black below; exterior: painted black band at top of rim above two dilute lines; below, incised spoked rosette with added red on alternate petals and on heart.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 360, no. B468)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0342) (Phase 1)
